  "description": "This specification defines how tarot data is encoded for spreads and readings.\n¶Spread YAML Required keys:\nspread: name of the spread. positions: ordered list of position definitions. draw: list of cards drawn with positions. Each position includes:\nname: position label. role: meaning or function in the spread. Each draw entry includes:\nposition: position name. card: card name. orientation: upright or reversed. Example:\nspread: three-card positions: - name: past role: the background or origin - name: present role: the current situation - name: future role: a likely direction draw: - position: past card: The Fool orientation: upright - position: present card: Two of Cups orientation: upright - position: future card: The Tower orientation: reversed ",
  "keywords": "tarot",
